result.name: Kam Fung Cafe

reviews.text: Old school Hong Kong cafe.  Portions are large, and tastes much better than the other cafes we have tried.  It is a very small cafe, with tight seating.  Loved the fact that you can substitute the dinner roll with pineapple bun with butter for an upcharge.  Be prepared to share a table when it gets busy.

Traditional local no frills 茶餐厅 (cafe) in Hong Kong. Small, cramp, but well kept and clean cafe. They serve breakfast/ brunch in sets or you can grab an ala carte freshly baked bun from the shop front. The shop is busy, but they don't rush the customers to finish the food. Set menu portion is actually a bit heavy, but I am not complaining. It is also cheap, given the taste and the portion. Must try is their pineapple buns!
Nothing special. It’s really small shop so be prepared to squeeze. Egg tart was ok but had better in central.

A friend defined this place as the definitive chaa Chang Teng experience and I can't help agree. I'm not a local but I felt like I travelled back in time when entering. The food came out quick and the taste of nostalgia was amazing. If you miss the old Hong Kong come here.

Ordered their famous "po-luo" buns (pineapple bread).
The service was good. Elderly man had been friendly and down to earth. I was given the freshest batch and the he was kind enough to filter out the buns which were slightly overbaked.

Buns were quite delicious. Not too sweet, and easy to chew. It certainly take years of experience to produce such mouthwatering buns. Authentic HK style
